definitions.definition: Very broad ; pertaining or appropriate to large classes or groups as opposed to specific instances.
examples: Capri pants can be a generic term for any cropped slim pants.

definitions.definition: lacking in precision, often in an evasive fashion; vague ; imprecise
not having a brand name ; nonproprietary in design or contents; fungible with the rest of its class.
Pertaining to genera of life instead of particular species thereof.
examples: There are scores of generic names within the order Decapoda, which includes many sea creatures that are called shrimp.

definitions.definition: specifying neither masculine nor feminine ; epicene ; unisex .
examples: Words like salesperson and firefighter are generic .
This included criticism of the generic use of man to include men and women.

definitions.definition: Written so as to operate on any data type , the type required being passed as a parameter .
Having coordinates that are algebraically independent over the base field.

examples: "That movie was so generic ; it was so such a bore"

main_definition: Very broad ; pertaining or appropriate to large classes or groups as opposed to specific instances.
secondary_definitions: lacking in precision, often in an evasive fashion; vague ; imprecise
( of a product or drug ) not having a brand name ; nonproprietary in design or contents; fungible with the rest of its class.
( taxonomy ) Pertaining to genera of life instead of particular species thereof.
( grammar , nonstandard ) specifying neither masculine nor feminine ; epicene ; unisex .
( computing , of procedures ) Written so as to operate on any data type , the type required being passed as a parameter .
